Chidiebube Okeoma, Owerri Members of a vigilante group, on Wednesday, rescued a kidnapped victim in a forest in the Abba community, Nwangele Local Government Area of Imo State. The vigilante group, the Abba Security Watch, was set up by the Abba Autonomous Community Development Union. The victim, a middle-aged man, was abducted by gunmen in the Ahiazu Mbaise Local Government Area of the state on Monday and was taken to a bush in the community, a source told our correspondent. Members of the vigilante group, who were on patrol, rescued the victim. He was said to have been shot in the leg by his abductors, who abandoned him on sighting the vigilantes. When contacted, the Police Public Relations Officer in the state, Orlando Ikeokwu, told our correspondent that the victim had been handed over to the personnel of the Nwangele Police Division. “I can confirm the development. He has been handed over to our men at the Nwangele Police Division. He was rescued by the vigilante group in a bush in Abba. He was kidnapped in Mbaise. We have already launched a manhunt for the fleeing kidnappers,” he said. Copyright PUNCH.
